        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 24 at 5:05PM EDT until July 24 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>SVRGRR

The National Weather Service in Grand Rapids has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Van Buren County in southwestern Michigan...

* Until 600 PM EDT.

* At 505 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Lake Michigan
Beach, or 9 miles north of Benton Heights, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
South Haven...         Paw Paw...             Hartford...
Mattawan...            Lawton...              Bangor...
Decatur...             Van Buren SP...        Lake Michigan
Beach...
Pine Grove...          Covert...              Keeler...
Lawrence...            Gobles...              Bloomingdale...
Breedsville...         Glendale...            Grand Junction...
Kendall...             South Haven Area Reg...
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
